  "Message": "fix: Docker build — lazy env validation, CI env vars for Playwright and Lighthouse (#6)\n\n* fix(docker): copy .npmrc before npm ci and drop obsolete compose version\n\nEnsures legacy-peer-deps=true is respected during the deps stage build.\nRemoves the deprecated top-level version field from docker-compose.yml.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(env,docker): lazy env validation and disable telemetry at build time\n\nenv.ts: replace top-level validation with getEnv() that returns {} during\nnext build (NEXT_PHASE=phase-production-build) instead of throwing, so\nruntime-injected variables don't need to be present at image build time.\n\nDockerfile: add NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1 to the builder stage to\nsuppress the telemetry notice during npm run build.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(ci): add required env vars to Playwright and Lighthouse jobs\n\nBoth jobs start the app server (next dev / next start respectively),\nso env.ts runs full validation — not the build-phase shortcut.\nThe old GITHUB_ACTIONS bypass was removed when validation was made\nlazy, so each job now supplies test-safe placeholder values for\nAUTH_SECRET, OAuth credentials, RESEND, and REDIS_URL.\n\nFor Lighthouse, the step-level DATABASE_URL placeholders still\noverride the job-level value for the Build and lhci autorun steps.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(ci): resolve gitleaks, Vitest env, and Pino build-phase failures\n\nGitleaks: add .github/workflows/ci.yml to the allowlist in\n.gitleaks.toml; change the two triggering placeholder values\n(AUTH_SECRET, RESEND_API_KEY) to strings that don't match\ngitleaks' generic-secret and resend-api-key rules.\n\nVitest: install dotenv (dev dep) and call config({ path: '.env.test' })\nat the top of src/tests/setup.ts so process.env is populated\nbefore test modules import env.ts. Update env.test.ts to replace\nthe removed GITHUB_ACTIONS bypass test with a test for the new\nNEXT_PHASE build-phase stub (verifies LOG_LEVEL:'silent' and\nNODE_ENV:'production' are returned).\n\nPino: change the build-phase stub in env.ts from {} to\n{ LOG_LEVEL: 'silent', NODE_ENV: 'production' } so pino()\nreceives a valid level string instead of undefined. Add a\n?? 'info' fallback in logger.ts as a secondary guard.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(test): load .env.test before any module imports via dedicated env-setup file\n\nES module imports are hoisted and evaluated before statements, so a\nconfig() call inside setup.ts runs after msw/server (and transitively\nenv.ts) has already been imported — too late for dotenv to help.\n\nSplit the dotenv bootstrap into src/tests/env-setup.ts and register\nit as the first entry in vitest.config.ts setupFiles. Vitest resolves\neach setup file fully before starting the next, so process.env is\npopulated before setup.ts imports msw/server which chains into env.ts.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(gitleaks): escape leading dot in ci.yml allowlist path regex\n\n* fix(ci): add postgres service and db push to Lighthouse job\n\nlhci autorun starts next start, which hits the database on real\npage requests. The placeholder DATABASE_URL caused a 500 on every\naudited URL.\n\n- Add postgres:16-alpine service container (matches Playwright job)\n- Add prisma db push step before the build so the schema exists\n- Remove DATABASE_URL override from the Run Lighthouse CI step so\n  it inherits the job-level URL pointing at the live service\n- Keep DATABASE_URL and NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED overrides on the\n  Build step (build phase shortcut means no real DB needed there)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(gitleaks): suppress historical placeholder leak via baseline file\n\nThe [[allowlists]] commits/stopwords/regexes fields in .gitleaks.toml\nare silently not applied to git-history findings in gitleaks 8.22.1 —\nonly --baseline-path suppresses historical findings reliably.\n\nGenerate .gitleaksbaseline containing the two known fingerprints from\ncommit 1d0e4be (AUTH_SECRET placeholder before it was shortened).\nUpdate the Detect secrets step to pass --baseline-path .gitleaksbaseline.\nClean up .gitleaks.toml by removing the two non-working allowlist\nentries added during diagnosis.\n\nVerified locally: 31 commits scanned, no leaks found.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(test): replace dotenv with process.loadEnvFile for env loading in Vitest\n\ndotenv v17 (dotenvx rebranded) was not reliably populating process.env\nbefore env.ts validation ran in CI. Replace with Node.js 20.12+ built-in\nprocess.loadEnvFile() called at the top of vitest.config.ts, which runs\nin the main process before any workers spawn so all workers inherit the\npopulated env. Remove dotenv devDependency and the now-unnecessary\nsrc/tests/env-setup.ts setupFile.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(test): silently skip loadEnvFile when .env.test is absent\n\nCI gets env vars from the job env block rather than .env.test,\nso throwing on a missing file would break CI runs. The try/catch\nmakes the call a no-op when the file doesn't exist while still\nloading it for local development.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(ci): add missing env vars to Vitest job\n\nThe Vitest job only had DATABASE_URL but env.ts requires all vars.\nAdd the same 10 placeholder env vars already present in the Playwright\nand Lighthouse jobs so CI passes without relying on .env.test.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(ci): add server startup diagnostic to Lighthouse job\n\nStarts the production server briefly before lhci autorun to capture\ncurl output and server logs, making it easier to diagnose 500 errors\nwithout having to re-run the full Lighthouse CI step blind.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(ci): add Redis service container to Vitest, Playwright, and Lighthouse jobs\n\nAll three jobs set REDIS_URL but had no Redis service, causing the app\nto crash at runtime trying to connect. Add redis:7-alpine with a\nhealth-check to each job so the service is ready before steps run.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n* fix(env): skip AUTH_URL HTTPS check when CI env var is set\n\nnext start always runs with NODE_ENV=production, including in CI where\nAUTH_URL is http://localhost:3000. Skip the HTTPS enforcement when the\nCI environment variable is present (set automatically by GitHub Actions)\nso local CI runs aren't blocked while real production deployments still\nrequire HTTPS. Update env.test.ts to stub CI=\"\" so the HTTPS tests\nremain meaningful in CI.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
